stri_split and extract

Source: R/8_fit.R
split_extract.Rd

stri_split and extract

nfactors(x, sep = guess_sep(x))

split_extract(x, i, sep = guess_sep(x))

Arguments

x

string
sep

string
i

integer

Value

character

Examples

require(magrittr)
file <- download_data('halama18.metabolon.xlsx')
object <- read_metabolon(file, plot=FALSE)

#> 	Read: C:\Users\abhagwa\AppData\Local\autonomics\autonomics\Cache/46a45da971ad_halama18.metabolon.xlsx
#> 		Log2 transform
x <- object$sample_id[1:5]
nfactors(x)

#> [1] 3
split_extract(x, 1:2)

#> [1] "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10"
split_extract(x, seq_len(nfactors(x)-1))

#> [1] "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10" "ctrl_h10"
split_extract(x, nfactors(x))

#> [1] "R1" "R2" "R3" "R4" "R5"

# With NA values
split_extract(fdata(object)$PUBCHEM, 1, ';')
